From 2cae6f75c6880e6909d9ec1c09d17d1a160916bf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: AltIsBacc <117834511+AltIsBacc@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 05:59:49 +0000
Subject: [PATCH v1 2/2] gui: pannable node-graph canvas for wiring pedals

Replace the fixed linear pedal strip (PedalArea) with GraphCanvas: a
pannable Rectangle where dropped pedal instances render as draggable
boxes with an input port (left) and output port (right), connected by
bezier wires. Dragging out of an output port and releasing over another
node's input port fires wire_completed(from_id, to_id); dragging the
canvas background pans it; right-clicking/right-pressing a node removes
it.

New GraphCanvasAdapter (view_adapters/graph_canvas.slint) exposes
nodes/wires as models plus pan_x/pan_y, and callbacks: node_dropped,
node_moved, node_removed, wire_completed, wire_removed. Nothing on the
Rust side is wired up to these yet, as requested - PedalArea and
PedalsAdapter.active_chain are left in place, just unused by the
fragment now, so nothing existing breaks.

Also extends Pedal (the picker tile) with drag_ended(type_id, x, y) so
a drop position can eventually be reported, and wires the pedal-picker
row into GraphCanvasAdapter.node_dropped with a cascading placeholder
position - Slint has no cross-component pointer tracking, so getting a
real canvas-space drop position out of the picker row needs a shared
ancestor tracking absolute pointer position across both; that's flagged
inline as a follow-up rather than faked.
